.SH "NAME"
zpipes \- elastic pipes proof of concept
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
zpipes servicename
.fi
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
Starts the zpipes service with a given name\&. To talk to the zpipes service you open a ZeroMQ DEALER socket and send commands in the form of multipart messages, then read replies\&. Supports two commands:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
PUT | pipename | opaque\-data
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
GET | pipename | size
.RE
.sp
Where size is an ascii integer, or empty/zero meaning "as much data as available"\&.
